# Photo Booth Project

Flutter photo booth app with AI transformations. Use this context when editing or adding code.

## Stack & platforms

- **Flutter** (SDK >=3.0.0 <4.0.0), **Provider** for state
- **Platforms**: iOS, Android (phones, tablets, Android TV). **Android minimum**: API 30 (Android 11). Web exists but is secondary (stubs for file/camera).
- **Camera**: Official Flutter `camera` plugin only; no custom native camera. External/USB cameras supported via `camera_android_camerax` (dependency override 0.7.1).
- **API**: Dio + Retrofit; base URL in `lib/utils/app_config.dart` (`AppConfig.baseUrl`).
- **Error reporting**: Bugsnag via `ErrorReportingManager` (disabled on web).

## Architecture: MVVM

- **Models**: `lib/models/` and screen-specific models (e.g. `theme_model.dart`, `photo_model.dart`).
- **ViewModels**: `ChangeNotifier` in `*_viewmodel.dart` next to the screen; business logic and API/session here.
- **Views**: Screens in `lib/screens/<feature>/` with `*_view.dart`; use `Provider` to read ViewModels. Reusable UI in `lib/views/widgets/`.
- **Services**: `lib/services/` — API, theme manager, session, file helper, print, share, error reporting. Prefer injecting services into ViewModels (constructor) for testability.

## Project structure

```
lib/
├── models/
├── screens/          # <feature>/<feature>_view.dart, <feature>_viewmodel.dart, models
├── services/         # API, theme, session, file, print, share, error_reporting
├── utils/            # app_config, constants, logger, exceptions, device_classifier
└── views/widgets/    # app_theme, app_scaffold, theme_card, full_screen_loader, etc.
```

- **Local package**: `packages/camera_native_details` (Android Camera2 details; stubs for iOS/Web).
- **Generated files**: `*.g.dart` (Retrofit, json_serializable) — do not edit; run `dart run build_runner build` if needed.
- **Assets**: `lib/images/` (e.g. launcher icon).

## Conventions

- **Config/URLs**: Change endpoints and links in `lib/utils/app_config.dart` only; no hardcoded API URLs elsewhere.
- **Logging**: Use `utils/logger.dart`; avoid `print`.
- **Errors**: Use `utils/exceptions.dart` (e.g. `ApiException`); report via `ErrorReportingManager` where appropriate.
- **Platform conditionals**: Use `kIsWeb`, or stub implementations (e.g. `file_helper_io.dart` vs `file_helper_web.dart`, `file_helper_stub.dart`) and `file_helper.dart` exports the right implementation.
